title: Confronting moment a cyclist taps on a car window and questions the passenger's manhood
description: The incident occurred on the streets of Rye on Melbourne's Mornington Peninsula on Tuesday morning, after the passenger antagonised one of the cyclist's friends.

title: Signature board director was forced out of position at NY college over unpaid bills
description: When addressing the missed payments back in 2019, Judith Huntington  blamed the bills on other staffers - who have since been fired - saying they failed to provide her with the information.

title: Entitled Medicare fraudster learns she will be jailed over brazen scam
description: A rampant fraudster who ripped-off sick Australians to pay for her lavish lifestyle hoped that getting pregnant would spare her from a stint in jail.

title: Stanford law school students line halls dressed in black masks as Judge Kyle Duncan row rumbles on
description: Jenny Martinez, the dean of Stanford Law School, found her classroom whiteboard defaced with protest fliers and the corridor outside her classroom lined with silent mask-wearing students.

title: Sheraton Grand Mirage hotel on Gold Coast built by Christopher Skase on the market for $200million
description: The crown jewel of Christopher Skase's colourful legacy, once known as a hangout for royalty and movie stars, is up for sale.

title: Hordes of Spring Breakers descend on Florida beaches and co-eds return to Fort Lauderdale
description: Hordes of students have descended upon Fort Lauderdale Beach as spring break in Florida gets into full swing.

title: AUKUS submarines deal: Ex-PM Paul Keating slams Albanese Labor government over nuclear subs
description: Former Labor prime minister Paul Keating has lashed the Albanese government over the AUKUS defence pact calling it 'worst deal in history'.

title: NSW election: Dad of seven Dominic Perrottet admits grocery shop out of control with inflation
description: The NSW Premier was asked about whether he is also feeling the pinch as household costs soar during his debate with Opposition Leader Chris Minns on Tuesday.

title: Roo-dunnit? Police release photo of wanted man who bears uncanny resemblance to ex-England ace Wayne
description: Northumbria Police posted an update on their Facebook page asking for help to trace the person they want to speak to in relation to an affray in South Shields, South Tyneside.

title: SARAH VINE: Why does Gary Lineker get lionised - while Fiona Bruce is hung out to dry?
description: SARAH VINE: Can you guess which one is lionised by the Left for being a free-speech hero and which one is condemned for making 'insensitive and irresponsible' comments?

title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: Hunt's mission is to supercharge growth
description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: Jeremy Hunt's rhetoric in advance of today's Budget has been bold and upbeat. He wants to 'supercharge growth', he says.

title: Police won't name driver involved in Cardiff car crash that killed three people
description: Eve Smith, Rafel Jeanne,  and Darcy Ross, were killed in the crash on March 4. South Wales Police said they will 'not be providing a running commentary' on their investigation.

title: Hip-hop hamsters and classical cats: How pets have different musical tastes
description: Half of our pets become excited when certain musical genres are played, a survey of UK owners discovered.

title: Teacher who stabbed her boyfriend to death told medics she heard 'voices'
description: Fiona Beal (left), 48, is accused of luring Nicholas Billingham (right), 42, to bed and stabbing him in the neck. She said she heard voices telling her to 'stand up' for herself before his death.

title: Toddler dies after hit by ride-on-mower at South Pambula on NSW far south
description: Crime scenes have been established at the hospital and at a property in South Pambula, south-east of Beg following the death of a toddler.

title: Top Admiral defends the £5bn boost for UK armed forces
description: Admiral Sir Tony Radakin (pictured) said the money was 'really good news' but hinted some capabilities would be 'pared down'.

title: Climate change protester Deanna 'Violet' Maree Coco avoids jail
description: A Sydney climate protester who was jailed for blocking peak-hour traffic on the Harbour Bridge has had her jail sentence overturned by a judge.

title: Aussie shark attack survivor Brett Connellan launches Stan documentary about his remarkable recovery
description: An Australian surfer who was attacked by a bull shark while paddling in water off the south coast of NSW has shared his story in a new documentary focusing on his remarkable road to recovery.

title: Adelaide woman Georgina Coventry wakes up from coma after car crash as GoFundMe started
description: Adelaide woman Georgina Coventry, who miraculously woke up from a coma after being involved in a terrifying car accident, has a long road to recovery.

title: Union rep sparks fury after telling striking doctors to not warn their NHS bosses
description: Dr Arjan Singh told medics there is no requirement to alert managers. He said industrial action has thrown payroll departments into chaos and doctors may not see their salaries docked.

title: ISIS bride fronts NSW court on charges she willingly entered Syria to join her husband
description: Mariam Raad, 31, faces 10 years jail after she was arrested in Young, NSW in January and charged with entering a part of Syria under the control of ISIS, in breach of federal law.

title: TV chef Antony Worrall Thompson's Oxfordshire restaurant was given a two star food hygiene rating
description: TV chef Anthony Worrall Thompson's restaurant in Oxfordshire was handed a new hygiene rating of only two stars out of five. The food safety officers' verdict has left him boiling over.

title: Freaky snake egg hatchlings find in Sydney family's backyard at Bringelly
description: Snake catcher Kane Durrant found 110 hatched eastern brown snake eggs under a slab where a clothesline once stood at the residence at Bringelly in Sydney's south-west last Thursday.

title: NSW Premier Dominic Perrottet flees out of a cafe door being chased by A Current Affair camera crew
description: NSW Premier Dominic Perrottet has been caught fleeing through a cafe from a camera crew after he was confronted over allegations his brothers were involved in shady deals.

title: SVB, Signature Bank and Credit Suisse donated $1.2M to Dems since 2017
description: The data is laid bare in an outline of the donations done up by government transparency group OpenSecrets - and shows that all three big banks spent big to ensure their candidates took office.

title: Claudia Lawrence's mother claims BBC is hounding the missing university chef for her TV licence fee
description: The university chef has not been seen since she failed to arrive for work at the University of York in March 2009, but letters have still been arriving at her property from the corporation.

title: Farewell to the 'King of the Serengeti': Fearsome lion named after Bob Marley is killed by rivals
description: Bob Junior - also known as Snyggve - was an incredibly photogenic big cat and a fan favourite with tour operators and visitors, who have paid tribute to him online. He was killed on Saturday.

title: Calls for tax cuts as job vacancies fall for eight month in a row and companies going bust doubles
description: Vacancies across the UK fell by 51,000 to 1.12million in the three months to February, figures from the Office for National Statistics showed.

title: EPHRAIM HARDCASTLE: Should Mick Lynch be getting his suit measured?
description: EPHRAIM HARDCASTLE: When George V was crowned in 1911 the TUC was invited to send two trade unionists as guests. Should Mick Lynch be getting measured at Moss Bros?

title: Victory for Alec Baldwin as Rust special prosecutor quits the case
description: Andrea Reeb has announced she is stepping down as special prosecutor in the trial of Alec Baldwin over the October 2021 Rust shooting.

title: Two boys charged with allegedly torturing and killing a ginger cat in Glenwood, in Sydney's west
description: Confronting vision shows the moment two teens run away with a family's cat before they allegedly torture, kill and dispose of the ginger feline in a nearby pond.

title: BBC Sport staff accused Gary Lineker of 'drawing picket lines' at crunch meeting with Tim Davie
description: It is understood that Mr Davie and the chief content officer Charlotte Moore headed up to BBC Sport's Media City offices in Salford, Manchester on Tuesday to address the controversy with staff.

title: Signature Bank boss hosted a company seminar on gender-neutral pronouns prior to bank failure
description: A seminar for gender-neutral pronouns held in October has critics of the embattled Signature Bank launching venomous attack on the company for appearing to not have their priorities in order.

title: Commonwealth Bank using Navigate to track staff mouse clicks, movement and when they are at desks
description: The Commonwealth Bank is cracking down on its workers by using a sneaky app that tracks exactly how often they're using their mouse and when they're physically at their desk.

title: Russian ambassador accuses US of 'provocation' and claims its fighter did not take out US drone
description: The Russian ambassador has accused the US of an 'act of provocation' and claims its fighter did not hit a US drone that crashed into the Black Sea on Tuesday.

title: Hancock's TikTok boasts more than 180,000 followers, but Government looks set to ban app
description: Matt Hancock is a contender for the title of Parliament's number one TikTok personality - despite growing security fears over the Chinese social media app.

title: Mackay father Mervinjames Rufil dies after workplace accident at All Metal Solutions in Paget
description: It is understood  Mervinjames Rufil was struck in the head by falling steel while operating machinery at All Metal Solutions in Paget, just south of Mackay last week

title: Adelaide car crash: Man drives into a home on Adam Road in Sheidow Park
description: A driver crashed into a parked car before ripping through a fence and crashing into a family home in Adelaide on Tuesday morning.

title: More than a third of investigations into violence against female victims are dropped, figures show
description: A national police report revealed 38 per cent of female victims withdrew from investigations despite officers knowing their alleged attacker's name.

title: Robert Smith release: Man who concealed Kiesha Abrahams' Mount Druitt murder to be paroled in April
description: Angry western Sydney locals have taken to the streets to protest the potential parole of Robert Smith (left), who concealed the murder of six-year-old Kiesha Abrahams in 2010.

title: Fyre Fest fraudster Billy McFarland to receive $19,000 to give  to German entrepreneurs
description: The creator of the disastrous Fyre Fest will make a paid appearance at an upcoming entrepreneurship summit in Germany but will have to fork over some of the money to his victims.

title: Deputy council leader ordered demolition of Wedgwood statue in Stoke
description: The 10ft red brick statue of the 18th-century pottery founder and abolitionist has stood in Festival Park in Stoke since 2009. But it was reduced to rubble earlier this year during work to widen a road.

title: Wheatsheaf Victoria: Man allegedly set on fire after fight with second man
description: A man, 69, has died after being allegedly set on fire during an altercation in the north-west Victorian town of Wheatsheaf, with a 63-year-old arrested at the scene and likely to face a murder charge.
